            <p>The airline also boasts one of the oldest fleets in the world with the average flight being above sixteen years old. The oldest flight models used by the airlines are the Boeing 737 – 300ER which have been in use since the last decade of the previous century – the nineteen nineties. These flights are generally among thirty to thirty – two years of age and are set to be retired nearly a decade later when a refurbishment of new models is set to arrive.</p>

            <p>The airline uses only flights from the Boeing aircraft company for its widebody flights but uses a mix of both Airbus and Boeing aircraft for its narrow-body flights with models such as Boeing 737 – 900ER, and Boeing 737-800ER being the most used among Boeing models with hundred and thirty-six of the first and a hundred and forty one of the latter.</p>

